COMPARE VSPHERE ESSENTIALS KITS











Compare 














Essentials Kit


Essentials Plus Kit






					Overview

Essentials Kit
					Server virtualization and consolidation with centralized management

Essentials Plus Kit 
					Server virtualization and consolidation plus business continuity




					Centralized Management

Essentials Kit
					vCenter Server Essentials

Essentials Plus Kit 
					vCenter Server Essentials




					License entitlement

Essentials Kit
					3 servers with up to 2 processors each

Essentials Plus Kit 
					3 servers with up to 2 processors each




					Features

Essentials Kit
					ESXi

Essentials Plus Kit 
					ESXi, vMotion, High Availability, Data Protection, vShield Endpoint, vSphere Replication








vSphere Essentials Kits are for small businesses and combine virtualization for up to three physical servers with centralized management with vCenter Server Essentials. Customers can purchase One Year Term Licenses for vSphere Essentials Kits and vSphere Essentials Plus Kits from the VMware store.

























VMware vSphere and vSphere with Operations Management can be purchased either through an all-in-one kit or a la carte editions. Kits are all-in-one offerings that deliver all the necessary licenses and features/functionality required to get virtualization running in an environment. Editions are a la carte offerings generally designed for larger or specific IT environments with a broader set of requirements.
 
Prices listed are for licenses only; Production, Basic Subscription and Support (SnS), and Incident Support (for vSphere Essentials Kit) are sold separately. Paid upgrades are available for all vSphere and vSphere with Operations Management offerings below to all higher kits or editions.
 
**Pricing information is only suggested retail pricing for the United States. Actual pricing may vary and is subject to change at any time. Please consult an authorized VMware partner or reseller for additional information.














