VMware vCloud Suite by VMware, Inc. | SDN & NFV Product 

























































 


 


 


















Open Menu





 






Directory > VMware, Inc. > VMware vCloud SuiteVMware vCloud Suite 






VMware, Inc.Corporate Headquarters3401 Hillview AvePalo Alto, California 94304United States1-877-486-927310,000+ employees OverviewReport EntriesDescriptionVMware vCloud® Suite delivers a comprehensive vSphere-based private cloud that greatly simplifies IT administration and provides optimum SLAs for all applications. 
VMware vCloud Suite contains these integrated products:
Infrastructure Platform

VMware vSphere®: Industry leading server virtualization platform.
Disaster Recovery Automation with VMware vCenter™ Site Recovery Manager™: Policy-based disaster recovery and testing for all virtualized applications.

Cloud Management Platform 

VMware vRealize™ Operations™: Intelligent performance, capacity, and configuration management for vSphere environments.
VMware vRealize Automation™: Self-service and policy-based infrastructure and application provisioning for vSphere environments.
VMware vRealize Business™: Automated costing, usage metering, and service pricing of virtualized infrastructure for vSphere environments. 

Cloud Provider Economics Through Policy-Driven Operations

Server virtualization – vCloud Suite is built on vSphere, the world’s leading server virtualization platform that delivers proven CapEx and OpEx savings of 40 percent to 60 percent.
Automated operations management – Dramatically increase utilization rates by proactively anticipating and responding to issues before they impact service quality—reducing capex up to 30 percent and boosting IT productivity by as much as 67 percent.
Capacity planning and optimization – Maximize infrastructure utilization by identifying idle and over-provisioned virtual machines and improving virtual machine density for applications. Powerful capacity modeling lets you optimize infrastructure spend by balancing cost with performance and risk.

Enabling Features

vSphere ESXi – Deploy the industry’s most capable bare-metal hypervisor, with a small disk footprint for high security and low maintenance.
DRS – Automatically balance loads across hosts to align resource allocation with business priorities.
vMotion — Implement live virtual machine migration to eliminate application downtime from planned server maintenance.
Storage DRS – Intelligently place and load-balance virtual machines based on I/O latency and storage capacity.
Storage vMotion – Employ proactive, non-disruptive storage migration to eliminate virtual machine storage I/O bottlenecks and free up valuable storage capacity.
VMFS – Simplify virtual machine provisioning and administrationwith a high-performance virtual machine-optimized cluster file system.
Comprehensive visibility – Leverage a single unified console to manage thousands of virtual machines, physical servers and applications across multiple datacenters.
Health and workload views – Benefit from visually intuitive real-time displays that reveal anomalies, faults and stressed workloads that can degrade infrastructure health and performance.
Performance analytics – Apply self-learning analytics that discover your environment’s behavior and adjust thresholds dynamically, freeing you from a flood of low-level metrics and alert storms.
Smart alerts – Receive proactive alerts accompanied by detailed metrics and root cause analyses, providing the context and intelligence to resolve potential issues in advance.
Advanced capacity management – Drill into detailed views and analytics that reveal under- and over-provisioned virtual machinesto guide you in reclaiming idle resources, increasing virtual machine densities and optimizing resource allocation.
Capacity trending and analysis – Gain insight into current and future resource needs and usage with performance trending, forward-looking projections and extended forecasts.
Heat map views – Quickly identify resource constraints and potential bottlenecks across the entire infrastructure through capacity-specific mapping.
Application HA – Gain high availability that is tied to specific applications.
Flash read cache – Accelerate performance for mission-critical applications by 5x to 10x with SSD virtualization combined with a host-based cache.
Replication – Use virtual machine-level replication by the vSphere host for more granular and flexible recovery options.
Data protection – Employ a back-up and recovery tool and appliance based on EMC Avamar.
Big-data extensions – Virtualize and elastically run big-data workloads, including all major Hadoop distributions.
Applications in Minutes via Automated Provisioning
Full abstraction of compute infrastructure – Abstraction, pooling and automation of the entire compute layer enables rapid application provisioning on any hardware stack and on vSphere-based private or public clouds.
Automated, policy-driven resource allocation – The right levels of resources are automatically assigned to applications and services, for optimum IT alignment with business policies, objectives and continually changing demands.
Self-service portal and catalog – An on-demand “IT storefront” allows designated managers to easily self-provision infrastructure, platform and desktop services, greatly reducing time-to-market for business initiatives

AvailabilityAvailablePackagingSoftware ApplicationData SheetDownloadCategoriesCloud and Virtualization > Cloud Management Platforms 


